				"text": "Commercial installation timeframes vary by project size and coating type. Polyaspartic systems can be back in service within 24-48 hours, while epoxy systems typically require 3-5 days. We work around your business schedule to minimize operational disruption."
			}
		},
		{
			"@type": "Question",
			"name": "What are the ROI benefits of commercial concrete coating?",
			"acceptedAnswer": {
				"@type": "Answer",
				"text": "Commercial concrete coatings provide significant ROI through reduced maintenance costs (up to 75% savings), improved worker safety, enhanced productivity, and compliance with health codes. Most businesses see payback within 2-3 years through operational savings."
			}
		},
		{
			"@type": "Question",
			"name": "Do commercial coatings meet health department requirements?",
			"acceptedAnswer": {
				"@type": "Answer",
				"text": "Yes, our commercial food service coatings are NSF-approved and meet FDA, USDA, and local health department requirements. They provide seamless, non-porous surfaces that resist bacteria and are easily sanitized."
			}
		},
		{
			"@type": "Question",
			"name": "Can you work around our business operations?",
			"acceptedAnswer": {
				"@type": "Answer",
				"text": "Absolutely. We specialize in phased installations, weekend work, and after-hours scheduling to minimize business disruption. Our fast-cure polyaspartic systems can often be completed with minimal downtime."
			}
		}
	]
};
